Claims CLAIMS: What is claimed: 1. An apparatus for releasably locking a stationary blade to a hair clipper, comprising: a stationary blade; a bracket configured for fixing said stationary blade to said hair clipper, said bracket having an opening; and an actuator having a locking formation engageable in said opening and operable between a first, locked position locking said stationary blade to said bracket, and a second, unlocked position releasing said stationary blade from said bracket. 2. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein said actuator further comprises: a lever having an arm with a free end and a pivot end; a barrel proximate said pivot end extending from said arm, having an outer periphery; a cam proximate said barrel, comprising: a lobe with an outer periphery having opposing ends; a neck connecting said lobe to said barrel, and having an outer periphery smaller than said outer periphery of said lobe, 

 wherein said lobe is inserted through said opening in said bracket at said second, unlocked position, and said lever is rotated to said first, locked position where said lever becomes locked. 3. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein said lever further comprises: a lobe axis which extends through said opposed ends of said lobe; and an arm axis which extends through said free end and said pivot end of said arm, wherein said lobe axis is inclined by an angle a relative to said arm axis. 4. The apparatus of claim 3, wherein said angle a is oblique, and more preferably, is 45 degrees. 5. The apparatus of claim 2, further including a stop, having opposed sides, proximate said free end and extending from said arm. 6. The apparatus of claim 5, wherein one of said opposed sides of said stop is closely adjacent to said bracket when said lever is in either said first, locked position or said second, unlocked position, and another of said opposed sides is closely adjacent to said bracket when said lever is in the other of said first, locked position or said second, unlocked position. 7. The apparatus of claim 2, further including a securing mechanism extending through said lever proximate said pivot end for attaching said barrel and said cam to said arm. 8. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein said locking formation has at least one locking stop configured for frictionally engaging said bracket in said locked position. 9. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein said stationary blade has a bracket opening aligned with said opening in said bracket, and said locking formation passes through said bracket opening and said opening in said bracket for securing said stationary blade to said bracket. 10. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein said neck displaces said lobe axially, such that said lobe accommodates a thickness of said bracket. 11. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein said opening of said bracket accommodates said outer periphery of said lobe. 12. The apparatus of claim 1, wherein said opening has an inner periphery, said inner periphery has chamfered edges, and wherein said lobe further comprises a lobe having a sloped shape proximate to a barrel end. 13. The apparatus of claim 2, wherein said barrel engages said arm at said pivot end, and said barrel and said pivot end are configured to be attached to each other using a keyed structure so that an axis of said lobe extends at a predetermined angle to an axis of said arm. 14. An apparatus for releasably locking a stationary blade to a hair clipper, comprising: a stationary blade; a bracket configured for fixing said stationary blade to said hair clipper, said bracket having an opening; and an actuator having a locking formation engageable in said opening and operable between a first, locked position locking said stationary blade to said bracket, and a second, unlocked position releasing said stationary blade from said bracket, said lever further comprising: said actuator being a lever having an arm with a free end and a pivot end; a barrel proximate said pivot end extending from said arm, having an outer periphery; 

 a stop having opposed sides, proximate said free end and extending from said arm, and wherein one of said opposed sides of said stop is in contact with said bracket when said lever is in either said first, locked position or said second, unlocked position, and another of said opposed sides is in contact with said bracket when said lever is in the other of said first, locked position or said second, unlocked position. 15. The apparatus of claim 14, further including: a cam proximate said barrel, comprising: a lobe with an outer periphery having opposing ends; a neck connecting said lobe to said barrel, and having an outer periphery smaller than said outer periphery of said lobe, and wherein said lobe is inserted through said opening in said bracket at said second, unlocked position, and said lever is rotated to said first, locked position where said lever becomes locked.
